01399 //  DIOI2C9AXISTRACKINGMPU9150::GetSlaveAddress
01400 //  Get the I2C address of the specified slave (0-3).
01401 //  Note that Bit 7 (MSB) controls read/write mode. If Bit 7 is set, it's a read
01402 //  operation, and if it is cleared, then it's a write operation. The remaining
01403 //  bits (6-0) are the 7-bit device address of the slave device.
01404 //
01405 //  In read mode, the result of the read is placed in the lowest available
01406 //  EXT_SENS_DATA register. For further information regarding the allocation of
01407 //  read results, please refer to the EXT_SENS_DATA register description
01408 //  (Registers 73 - 96).
01409 //
01410 //  The MPU-6050 supports a total of five slaves, but Slave 4 has unique
01411 //  characteristics, and so it has its own functions (getSlave4* and setSlave4*).
01412 //
01413 //  I2C data transactions are performed at the Sample Rate, as defined in
01414 //  Register 25. The user is responsible for ensuring that I2C data transactions
01415 //  to and from each enabled Slave can be completed within a single period of the
01416 //  Sample Rate.
01417 //
01418 //  The I2C slave access rate can be reduced relative to the Sample Rate. This
01419 //  reduced access rate is determined by I2C_MST_DLY (Register 52). Whether a
01420 //  slave's access rate is reduced relative to the Sample Rate is determined by
01421 //  I2C_MST_DELAY_CTRL (Register 103).
01422 //
01423 //  The processing order for the slaves is fixed. The sequence followed for
01424 //  processing the slaves is Slave 0, Slave 1, Slave 2, Slave 3 and Slave 4. If a
01425 //  particular Slave is disabled it will be skipped.
01426 //
01427 //  Each slave can either be accessed at the sample rate or at a reduced sample
01428 //  rate. In a case where some slaves are accessed at the Sample Rate and some
01429 //  slaves are accessed at the reduced rate, the sequence of accessing the slaves
01430 //  (Slave 0 to Slave 4) is still followed. However, the reduced rate slaves will
01431 //  be skipped if their access rate dictates that they should not be accessed
01432 //  during that particular cycle. For further information regarding the reduced
01433 //  access rate, please refer to Register 52. Whether a slave is accessed at the
01434 //  Sample Rate or at the reduced rate is determined by the Delay Enable bits in
01435 //  Register 103.
01436 //
01437 //  ""
01438 //  @version      04/07/2016 1:11:52
01439 //
01440 //  @return       XBYTE : Current address for specified slave
01441 //
01442 //  @param        num :  Slave number (0-3)
01443 -----------------------------------------------------------------*/
01444 XBYTE DIOI2C9AXISTRACKINGMPU9150::GetSlaveAddress(XBYTE num)
01445 {
01446   if(num > 3) return 0;
01447 
01448   ReadByte(deviceaddr, DIOI2CMPU9150_RA_I2C_SLV0_ADDR + num*3, buffer);
01449   return buffer[0];
01450 }
01451 
01452 
